/* Input is a space-delimited string of numberals from 'zeros' to 'nine'. Valid choices was 'zeros', 'one', 'two', 'three', 'four', 'five','six','seven', 'eight' and 'nine'. Return the string with numbers sort from smaller to larger
  >>> sortNumbers('three one five')
  'one three five'
